impl Cache

pub fn new(nal_config: NALConfig) -> Self

Creates a new Cache instance. Try to open a database file. If file not exists - try to create it. If there already present “nal_map” table and “idx_key” in DB - does nothing. If not - creates it.

Checks if node presents in cache.

pub fn node_get(
    &mut self,
    key: &NodeEpKey,
    value: &mut Attributes
) -> Result<(), String>

Gets a value for the given key. If node with such key doesn’t present in DB - returns an error.

pub fn node_set(
    &mut self,
    key: &NodeEpKey,
    attributes_new: &Attributes
) -> Result<(), String>

Updates a value for the given key. If node with such key doesn’t present in DB - creates it.

pub fn node_remove(&mut self, key: &NodeEpKey) -> Result<(), String>

Removes a node from the cache. Here is no necessity to check if node presents in cache.

pub fn get_all_nodes(&mut self) -> Result<Vec<NodeEpKey>, Error>

    &mut self,

Gets all delayed messages data (topic, payload) with requested UNID. Deletes all these messages trom the table.
